</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="12" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[192,1440,1571,1659]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,317,1571,1595]" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scarbrough" authorityYear="2008" box="[331,530,1572,1595]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Ommatius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="12" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tepui">
<emphasis box="[331,530,1572,1595]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="12">Ommatius tepui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from congeners by the characters in the key and the combined characters of the male terminalia (Fig. 42-48), especially the apically flattened, slightly up-turned epandrium with a truncate apex, and the long, wide, flattened gonocoxal process.
</paragraph>
